<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nikolos Rovani</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-25 11:45:23</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>First. It is true that once you make level 10, Kalatrina<BR>
wont give you the quest, but you can start it by having a<BR>
level 1 to 9 paladin start it, and hand you the letter.<BR>
once you have the letter (it is not no drop) you then<BR>
continue from there.<BR>
<BR>
Second, Guard Alayel is found out in the back courtyard<BR>
of the militia house, he will be standing in the shadows<BR>
under the balcony. Handing him the nate will cause the<BR>
corrupt guards to kill him. So if he is not there, just<BR>
wait around for him to respawn or go do other things and<BR>
keep checking back frequenly.<BR>
<BR>
Third, it was stated that once you do your testimony quest<BR>
you will automatically become KOS to Freeport Militia. This<BR>
is NOT TRUE. I did my testimony quest at level 5 (with help)<BR>
and am now level 42, and have killed a few militia and <BR>
turned in thier helms for the bounty, and I am still not<BR>
KOS. But I am very close to it. Point is, getting your <BR>
Testimony DOES NOT make you KOS.<BR>
<BR>
It was also asked if 2 people can turn in items like you<BR>
can do on JBoots quest. No. Most items in the SoulFire <BR>
quest are no drop, and for some reason, this is one of the <BR>
many quests that somehow keep track of who hands what. So<BR>
the person doing the quest has to be the one turning in the<BR>
items. Perhaps it was dont as this is one of the Paladins<BR>
Holy sword, and as a Paladin, you shouldn't cheat the quest.<BR>
<BR>
Also, when you give the first note to kalatrina, she keeps<BR>
it. You can get a second not by restarting the quest. Or, <BR>
instead of giving Kalatrina the note, you are able to skip<BR>
that step. If you just keep the note, and go straight to<BR>
the office of the people, you can get the information you<BR>
need to inform Kalatrina of. NOTE: You CANNOT just tell<BR>
Kalatrina that Zimel's Blades has been condemned without<BR>
going to the Office of The People. You MUST have the person<BR>
in the Office Of The People tell you it was condemned and<BR>
THEN you can tell Kalatrina.<BR>
<BR>
Non human Paladins may have to do some faction work for The<BR>
Knights Of Truth. It's best to start your Testimony and <BR>
SoulFire quest with an AMIABLE faction rating. Knights of<BR>
Truth faction is easy. In West Freeport Newbie Area, and in<BR>
East Commons, just kill every orc you see. Your faction will<BR>
go up rapidly.<BR>
<BR>
The only part of the quest that is near impossible now is<BR>
the Sir Lucan fight. While before it required a couple<BR>
good high level groups, now with the beefed up gate guards<BR>
it's basically a suicide mission. But there is a tactic that<BR>
will work, if it is done right. Follow this line of attack<BR>
for the Lucan fight.<BR>
<BR>
#1. Position your 2 high level  groups near the West<BR>
Freeport / East Commons zone border. Anyone in the combat<BR>
groups that are KoS to FP Militia should stay clear as to<BR>
not attract a fight before it is wanted.<BR>
<BR>
#2. Position a "detainer" (can be any level, as long as<BR>
they are not KoS to militis) near the zone. This should <BR>
only be 1 person, and they can be a member of one of the<BR>
groups if you desire. They have a specific job to do<BR>
just before the fight, so make sure they stay alert.<BR>
<BR>
#3. You need a runner. MAKE SURE this person had SoW, and<BR>
is not KoS to Militia. A shaman would work best, as they<BR>
have the self only speed boost of Spirit of the Cheeta.<BR>
It is this persons job to start the whole fight, so MAKE<BR>
SURE they are NOT in either of the combat groups.<BR>
<BR>
#4. Your runner, SoW equiped, must know the militia house<BR>
well. Have them go in, and enguage Sir Lucan. Once they<BR>
do this, damn near every miltia around will be out for their <BR>
blood. Once the runner enguages Sir Lucan, they immediately<BR>
make a break for the East Commons Zone. Make good use of<BR>
Spirit of the Cheeta. The runner should know EXACTLY where<BR>
the "Detainer" is, and zone there.<BR>
<BR>
#5. Once the runner zones, the Detainer should quickly target <BR>
Sir Lucan and HAIL him. Do not hail untill AFTER the runner<BR>
zones, and make sure Detainer and Runner are not grouped <BR>
together or Sir Lucan will attack. The Detainer should KEEP<BR>
HAILING Sir Lucan OVER AND OVER. This will cause Sir lucan<BR>
to stay at the zone, while the other guards that trained out<BR>
after the runner will return to their posts.<BR>
<BR>
#6. Once all the other guards leave, and are VERY FAR away <BR>
from Lucan, then both combat groups should be safe to move<BR>
in and take Lucan out. I do not know if Lucan will try to<BR>
flee when he gets low on health, so he should be rooted as<BR>
much as possible towards the end of combat. Or at the very<BR>
least, he should be snared.<BR>
<BR>
#7. Once you kill Sir Lucan, his Skeleton will rise up and<BR>
attack, you must kill his skelleton also.<BR>
<BR>
#8. It may be a good idea to have reserve people standing<BR>
by, so that if anyone in a group dies, the group leader can<BR>
remove the dead group member and invite a fresh body into<BR>
the group to assist. Make sure all group members agree that<BR>
if they fall in combat, it is ok to remove and replace them.<BR>
<BR>
(note: this is only an RP suggestion, as any people standing<BR>
by can assist in the lucan fight, they just will not likely<BR>
get any experience.)<BR>
<BR>
If all the steps are exicuted correctly and safely, Lucan<BR>
should be taken out without too many losses.<BR>
<BR>
BE FORWARNED: This portion of the SoulFire quest will make<BR>
quite a few people in the groups KoS to Freeport militia.<BR>
if you are in a group, and do not wish to be KoS, I <BR>
suggest you take the following steps:<BR>
<BR>
First, make sure the groups know that you dont want to be<BR>
KoS, and make sure they dont have a problem with these<BR>
steps.<BR>
<BR>
Second, just before lucan is about to fall, I suggest you<BR>
drop from group and ZONE IMMEDIATELY! This should wipe<BR>
agro, and after Lucan is killed, you shouldnt take any<BR>
faction hits.<BR>
<BR>
Please keep in mind, this will leave groups short, and <BR>
Lucan's skelleton must still be killed. So by doing<BR>
this, you could jepordize the entire mission.<BR>
<BR>
Also keep in mind, this fight is usually done on the<BR>
behalf of one paladin. This paladin must be the one to <BR>
loot the corpses. This is an "HONOR FIGHT". So all people<BR>
participating should be certain that there is a HIGH<BR>
PROBABILITY that they may die. If you have a problem with<BR>
this, DO NOT AGREE TO HELP.<BR>
<BR>
There is nothing more frustraiting than organizing a <BR>
major event like this, only to have people back out at the<BR>
last minute because they dont want to be KoS or loose any<BR>
experience.<BR>
<BR>
All participants should know AND ACCEPT THE FACT that they<BR>
may end up KoS and they may loose a little experience. But,<BR>
assisting a Paladin in recieving their Holy Sword (if the<BR>
Paladin is worth of the title "Paladin") will ensure that<BR>
the next time you are in need of a group of people to <BR>
assist you in a quest, you will be sure of atleast 1 person<BR>
that wont let you down.<BR>
<BR>
And my advice to all Paladins who recieve their SoulFire:<BR>
<BR>
Keep a list of names by your computer. Write down the name<BR>
of every person that helps you in this quest, and remember<BR>
them. Upon recieving SoulFire, you will owe these people<BR>
a great debt. DO NOT abandon them. If they ever need<BR>
assistance with anything, your name SHOULD be at the top<BR>
of the list of people assisting them.<BR>
<BR>
After all, Honor is the way of the Paladin.<BR>
<BR>
Nikolos Rovani: Paladin of Marr, Karana Server.<BR>
