<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nikolos Rovani</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-05 13:09:45</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Thanx :-)<BR>
<BR>
The question about Faction for Brother Hayle. I am somewhat<BR>
curious myself. First, he is a Paladin (Cleric?) from Qeynos<BR>
and I raised my faction using 2 small quests. First, you can <BR>
turn in the red bandit sashes to the Temple of Thunder in<BR>
Qeynos. I forget which paladin you turn them into. I believe<BR>
it is the paladin standing outside of the building on what <BR>
looks like a large area rug. He is standing next to a<BR>
merchant that sells shields. Although I am not 100% confident<BR>
of my memory on this, I suggest you talk to all the NPC's to<BR>
see which offers the quest, or at the very least, do a few<BR>
/shouts and ask if anyone in zone knows.<BR>
<BR>
Second, if I am not mistaken, there is also a newbie "Box Of<BR>
Bone Chips" quest you can do. I dont remember if this one is<BR>
given in the Temple of Life or House of Thunder. Again, would<BR>
be best to check around. My advice, go to Tox, make your way <BR>
into the Newbie area of Paineel. Take ALOT of empty packs, as<BR>
I spent about 2 hours killing skells, and in 2 hours, I filled<BR>
6 back packs full of stacks of 20 bone chips. Wall to wall<BR>
Skells here, not alot of people, no experience, but you will<BR>
get all the bone chips you can carry in a very short time.<BR>
<BR>
I was also told once that there is a way to "buy" faction. I<BR>
tried this with a compairable cleric in Erudin, and it didnt<BR>
work, but 2 bro's of mine did do it in Qeynos and raised their<BR>
faction in this manner. Look for a cleric in the Temple of Life<BR>
who (when haild) offers to heal you or cure your disease or<BR>
poison. Pay him 4 gold for a quick heal spell. You will hear<BR>
the trumpets sound like you recieved experience. You will not<BR>
get an experience message and will not actually gain experience<BR>
but at the time they did it, you did recieve positive faction.<BR>
(NOTE: Ofcourse, this was quite some time ago, and we all know<BR>
Verant, when they discover something in the game that works<BR>
to OUR advantage, it must immediately be "fixed" so that you<BR>
cannot achieve your goals)  :-)<BR>
<BR>
Now, someone mentioned that in order to recieve SoulFire from<BR>
Brother hayle, you must have ATLEST Kindly faction. I was <BR>
also told by people on the Karana server (when I did shouts<BR>
asking what my faction needs to be) about 50% of the people<BR>
shouted back that faction needs to be Kindly or better, and <BR>
the other 50% shouted back that it has to be WARMLY.<BR>
(and ofcourse, when I shouted "HOW MANY OF YOU ARE ABSOLUTELY<BR>
POSITIVE?" The response was, 100% of them were positive.) So<BR>
Your guess is as good as mine. But, since I have all the items<BR>
and all I have left to do is to trade them all for Soulfire<BR>
I figure my advice would be to do what I am going to do. Play<BR>
it safe. Just bite down, do the faction work, and raise your<BR>
faction to "WARMLY" which is the highest faction, and then<BR>
you'll know for sure that when you trade the quest items<BR>
in you will recieve SoulFire.<BR>
<BR>
About the question of how to do the "Brother Hayle" portion:<BR>
<BR>
First, take the letter you got from the bank in High Keep, and<BR>
go to SplitPaw. IMPORTANT: Bring a friend. Preferably one that<BR>
can cast invisibility on you. If you cant get someone that can<BR>
cast invisibility, bring anyone you want, and spend a few platinum<BR>
and get you both ATLEAST 2 Invis Potions each. At Any rate, <BR>
YOU WILL NEED ANOTHER PERSON WITH YOU.<BR>
<BR>
Print out a map of paw so that you can find the jail cells. Go<BR>
into Paw, and make your way to the cell blocks. Hayle is in the <BR>
last cell at the end of the passage. <BR>
<BR>
There are levers on the wall that operate a couple cells at<BR>
a time. Search for the lever that opens Brother Hayle's cell.<BR>
Once you open the cell, go in and hail him.<BR>
<BR>
NOTE: If you were smart, you used 1 invis potion to get to the<BR>
cell. Hayle will not talk to you while you are invisible, and he<BR>
con indifferent. To get an accurate reading of your "con<BR>
status" you must make yourself visible.<BR>
<BR>
Hand the letter to Hayle, and you will recieve faction, experience, <BR>
he will tell you what items he requires from you. He will also<BR>
give you a new copy of the letter. Keep it, you'll need to<BR>
give it back to him again when you turn in everything else.<BR>
<BR>
Once you kill Lucan and trade his testimony for the<BR>
"Brilliant Sword Of Faith", and get the Glowing Sword Hilt<BR>
from Xicotl in Mistmoor, you need to take the sword of faith,<BR>
the glowing hilt, YOUR testimony, and the letter that Hayle gave<BR>
back to you, and return them all to Brother hayle again.<BR>
<BR>
NOTE: Once you enter the cell to talk to hayle, the jail<BR>
cell door will close locking you in. Hence the need for a friend.<BR>
Make sure your friend DOES NOT enter the cell. When you are<BR>
finished with your business, they need to throw the lever<BR>
again to let you out. Then you can either teleport out of<BR>
Paw (if your friend has that ability) or drink your second<BR>
invis potion and walk (run) back out.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helped, if ya need anything else, just E-Mail me<BR>
(my e-address is on my previous post or look me up on the<BR>
Karana Server)<BR>
<BR>
Nikolos "If Marr wanted me to fly/levitate he'd buy me a ticket on Delta" Rovani<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
