<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Oops... me again... forgot to answer the other question:<BR>
<BR>
Grofflah Steadirt: When he spawns? At night. But you have<BR>
to keep in mind, Verant played a rude trick on us. For Paladins<BR>
to get their swords, we must enlist the aid (information) of<BR>
Grofflah Steadirt. But, the forces of evil are constantly<BR>
working against us. The ultimate evil (i.e. Verant) has also<BR>
included Grofflah in a second quest. That of the darker classes,<BR>
and in THEIR quest, they must PREVENT Grofflah from divulging<BR>
sensitive information that Sir Lucan does not want him imparting<BR>
to any would be seekers of a certain sword that Lucan himself<BR>
wishes to aquire. So, Lucan has gone out of his way to convince<BR>
some of the "less moral elements" of Norrathian society to<BR>
"silence" Grofflah once and for all.<BR>
<BR>
In Short, you need Grofflah to show up to give you information <BR>
you need for your quest. And at the same time, there are others<BR>
who need to KILL Grofflah. So, it's pot luck.<BR>
<BR>
Give him the note, and then do what he says. Go to the Seafarers<BR>
Roost and wait for him. He will show up durring the night time<BR>
hours (if he has not be otherwise detained or killed). Once<BR>
the morning comes, if he has not showed up, all you can do is go<BR>
back to Grofflah's and try again.<BR>
<BR>
Stick with it, sooner or later you will see him and get the<BR>
information you need.<BR>
<BR>
Nikolos "How did I loose my level AGAIN?" Rovani</font></td></tr></table>
